This folder contain the files necessary to reproduce the single structures used in the manuscript. 

Interactoin matrix are stored in npy files(with intmat or inter_mat in their names). Here we provide the interaction matrices for free polymer, uniformly attractive polymer, single domain polymers with 3X, 10X and 100X interaction inside and outside of the domain and polymer with two domains that are 1,5 and 9 regions away from each other.

MVN_sampling_and_distance_calculation.ipynb is the jupyter notebook that perform the sampling. It reads interaction matrices as input and generate 3d coordinates and pairwise distance matrices.

StructureSampling.py contains the functions used in MVN_sampling_and_distance_calculation.ipynb


